The date of this letter will I hope explain to you why we have not been able to avail ourselves of your kind and welcome invitation, which only arrived here last night.<note>Morgan captained the Southampton on its inaugural voyage across the Atlantic in June 1849. It docked at Gravesend on 6 July (‘Money-Market and City Intelligence’, <hi rend="italic">Times</hi>, 6 July 1849), and then travelled on to London. It left London for the return journey to New York on 28 July (‘Regular Line of Packets between London and New York’, <hi rend="italic">Times</hi>, 4 June 1849).</note>
